"lips and buccal mucosal lining oral alimentary cavity, external approach. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the lips and buccal mucosal lining of the oral alimentary cavity with external approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0c.. . "
"lips and buccal mucosal lining oral alimentary cavity, external approach. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the lips and buccal mucosal lining of the oral alimentary cavity with external approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0c.. supplement lower gingiva with nonautologous tissue substitute,  external approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to supplement lower gingiva with nonautologous tissue substitute,  external approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0cu6xkz. "

"mouth alimentary cavity face throat neck, percutaneous approach. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the mouth or alimentary cavity of the face and throat and neck with percutaneous approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0c.. revision of nonautologous tissue substitute in mouth and throat,  percutaneous approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to revision of nonautologous tissue substitute in mouth and throat,  percutaneous approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0cwy3kz. "

"oropharyngeal bony palate/cartilaginous structures mouth, external approach. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the oropharyngeal bony palate and cartilaginous  structures of the mouth with external approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0c.. extirpation of matter from lower tooth,  all,  external approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to extirpation of matter from lower tooth,  all,  external approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0ccxxz2. "

"oropharyngeal bony palate/cartilaginous structures mouth, open approach. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the oropharyngeal bony palate and cartilaginous structures of the mouth with open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0c.. reposition lower tooth,  multiple,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to reposition lower tooth,  multiple,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0csx0z1. "

"oropharyngeal bony palate/cartilaginous structures mouth, open approach. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the oropharyngeal bony palate and cartilaginous structures of the mouth with open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0c.. release hard palate,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to release hard palate,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0cn20zz. "
"oropharyngeal bony palate/cartilaginous structures mouth, open approach. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the oropharyngeal bony palate and cartilaginous structures of the mouth with open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0c.. reattachment of lower tooth,  all,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to reattachment of lower tooth,  all,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0cmx0z2. "oropharyngeal bony palate/cartilaginous structures mouth, percutaneous approach. this class includes one or more of 23 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the structures of the oropharyngeal bony palate and cartilaginous structures of the mouth with percutaneous approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 0c.. release hard palate,  percutaneous approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to release hard palate,  percutaneous approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 0cn23zz. "
